Title: A Geometrical Formulation of the Renormalization Group Method for Global
  Analysis
Author: Teiji Kunihiro
Comments: Errors in Eq. (4.14) and (4.18) are corrected. Due comments are
  added. To be published in Prog. Theor. Phys.(Kyoto) vol.94, No.4 (1995)
Subj-class: High Energy Physics - Theory; Functional Analysis; Pattern
  Formation and Solitons
Journal-ref: Prog.Theor.Phys. 94 (1995) 503-514; Erratum-ibid. 95 (1996) 835
\\
  On the basis of the classical theory of envelopes, we formulate the
renormalization group (RG) method for global analysis, recently proposed by
Goldenfeld et al. It is clarified why the RG equation improves things.
